==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nihilism
<hw>Ni"hil*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>nihil</ets> nothing: cf. F. <ets>nihilisme</ets>. See
<er>Annihilate</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Nothingness;
nihility.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The doctrine that nothing can be known; scepticism
as to all knowledge and all reality.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Politics)</fld> <def>The theories and practices of
the Nihilists.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nihilist</ent>⟦br⟧
